      "author": "zrodgers (Zach)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hello Everyone, I would like to make a function or an automation for a due date. I have 2 different dates and i want the status color to change if date1 is passed date 2. Is this possible? Its just for a quick visual to make sure our estimated completion date is before our actual due date. These are also subitems if it matters.</p>\n<p>Example of what it should look like…<br />\n<img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/b/f/bf7bb406b82316c3070f4390953c82a6a19850f0.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"621\" height=\"129\" /></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": 116816,
      "postNumber": 2,
      "createdAt": "2023-02-23T19:58:06.172Z",
      "author": "afernandezredk (Antonio)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hi <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/zrodgers\">@zrodgers</a>, you can use a formula column with emojis:<br />\n<img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/e/2/e2c095927b50c7d69e10ebc4a2aff3376d7bac58.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"410\" height=\"146\" /></p>\n<p>IF({Date}&gt;{Date 1},“<img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/green_circle.png?v=12\" title=\":green_circle:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":green_circle:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />”, “<img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/red_circle.png?v=12\" title=\":red_circle:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":red_circle:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />”)</p>"
    },
